<handDesc>
<handNote script="Ethiopic" xml:id="h1">
<desc>The manuscript shows many palaeographic peculiarities not mentioned in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/MIBCP4VG"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Uhlig1988Palaographie"/><title level="m">Äthiopische Paläographie</title><title level="s">Äthiopistische Forschungen</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Siegbert</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Uhlig</t:surname></author><pubPlace>Stuttgart</pubPlace><publisher>Franz Steiner Verlag</publisher><date>1988</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Äthiopistische Forschungen</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">22</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">22</biblScope></bibl> e.g.
a) some of the fourth-row signs (ላ ባ ጻ ሳ) are written with a right leg broken but the same length as the left leg b) some of the
seventh-row signs (ሖ ኮ አ) have legs of the same length and a little stroke attached to the bottom part of the left leg c) the sign
ፈ occasionally resembles ፎ d) the stroke on top of ስ is L-shaped e) the loop in ዓ is very large.</desc>
</handNote>
</handDesc>

